---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
import StudyDataTable from "@/components/studydatatable.astro";
---

<Layout title="Safety - CleanAirHats">
  <Container>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold my-6">
      Safety: Proven 3 Times Safer Than N95 Mask
    </h1>
    <div class="mt-2 w-full">
      <p class="mb-4 text-gray-700">
        MyAirHat™ offers significant safety advantages:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 mb-4 text-gray-700">
        <li>
          <strong>Integral face shield protects eyes:</strong> Provides built-in
          eye protection against droplets and aerosols that happen when others cough
          and sneeze.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No leaks due to poor fit:</strong> Unlike masks that rely on a
          tight seal against the face (which is often imperfect), MyAirHat™ creates
          a separated air environment.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <StudyDataTable />
      <div class="mt-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">
          Carbon Dioxide Effects on Submarine-Qualified Sailors
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          Ryder et al., Aerospace Medicine and Human Performance (2018)
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">
          A 2018 study showed no significant differences in decision making
          between sailors exposed to 600, 2500, or 15,000 ppm CO₂ for 80
          minutes. <a
            href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29789085/"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
            target="_blank">Read the study</a
          >
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">
          Today the U.S. Navy's recommended carbon dioxide exposure limits for
          submarines are 25,000 ppm (2.5%) for periods up to 24 hours, and 8,000
          ppm (0.8%) for durations up to 90 days. (See Table 3-3 at <a
            href="https://nap.nationalacademies.org/read/11170/chapter/5#59"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
            target="_blank">nap.nationalacademies.org/read/11170/chapter/5#59</a
          >.)
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>

